bcl:definition.bcl:text:
  exposure means any contact with, or ingestion, inhalation or
assimilation of, a tobacco product, including any smoke or other by-product of the use,
consumption or combustion of a tobacco product;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
other expenditures, made directly or through one or more agents or other
            intermediate bodies, by the government for programs, services, benefits or similar
            matters associated with disease;

bcl:definition.bcl:text:
  promote or promotion includes, for a tobacco
product, the marketing, distribution or sale of the tobacco product and research with
respect to the tobacco product;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
in an action under section 2 (1), a breach of a common law, equitable or
            statutory duty or obligation owed by a manufacturer to persons in British Columbia who
            have been exposed or might become exposed to a tobacco product;

oasis:entry.oasis:line:
the defendant's market share for the type of tobacco product from the
                    date of the earliest tobacco-related wrong committed by that defendant to the
                    date of trial;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
the degree to which a defendant collaborated or acted in concert with other
            manufacturers in any conduct that caused, contributed to or aggravated the risk of
            disease;

the extent to which a defendant continued manufacture or promotion of the type
            of tobacco product after it knew or ought to have known of the risk of disease resulting
            from exposure to the type of tobacco product;
